main event: A possible satellite sighting with the brightness of a first magnitude star, moving east at a speed of 10 degrees per minute, was reported in the Pacific Ocean.
interesting points: The sighting was described as a possible satellite, with the brightness of a first magnitude star.
The object was reported to be moving east at a speed of 10 degrees per minute.
The location of the sighting was in the Pacific Ocean at coordinates 35.10N 174.40W.
The sighting was reported to various military organizations, including COMBARFORPAC, COMHAWSEFRON, CINCPACAF, and CINCNORAD.
The report notes that an advance copy of the sighting was delivered to XOPX, NIN, and DIA, and the message was readdressed to the CIA.
